cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to solve relational tasks, specifically question similarity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method to inject structural representations in NNs, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses SVM and Tree Kernels, which are commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) research. Finally, the paper uses large corpora and pre-training techniques, which are also relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
